data.description: Beautiful Historic home in the heart of South Routt! This charming 3+ bedroom, 1 bathroom home in Phippsburg is a turn of the century home on a large, corner lot that is fully fenced.  Many upgrades have been made throughout, with room for a few of your personal touches.   Enjoy two levels of living spaces with a walkout garden level basement.  There are 2 rooms on the upper level that could be used as a bedroom, office, or workout space, and 2 rooms on the lower level for similar use.  There are so many unique features, including a vintage original sink in the kitchen!  Enjoy cozy winter nights around the wood stove on the walk out lower level.  Location off of Pine street gives plenty of off street parking and access to the spacious yard, garage, and home.  This property is conveniently located near the Flat Tops Supply Store for your construction and farm needs.  Less than 4 miles to the restaurants and shops of Oak Creek, 23 miles to City Market in Steamboat, and 8 miles to the Stagecoach Marina for your Summer Lake days!  Ideal for access between the Yampa School and Soroco High School locations.  This home is on the Routt County Historic Societies Registry and has quite the history and roots in the South Routt Community. This property also qualifies to build a Secondary Dwelling unit onsite.  Come tour and see the historic charm and quiet living that Phippsburg has to offer.
